nodes.title: Pass 1 with Enhancements vs Pass 2 with Enhancements
FreeU_V2 recommended
widgets_values:
OFFICIAL SDXL settings:
b1: 1.3 (range: 1 ≤ b1 ≤ 1.2)
b2: 1.4 (range: 1.2 ≤ b2 ≤ 1.6)
s1: 0.9 (range: s1 ≤ 1)
s2: 0.2 (range: s2 ≤ 1)

Description of settings: 

b1: larger areas; > 1 increases contrast and saturation but may lose small details, < 1 causes artifacts

b2: smaller areas; > 1 increases contrast and saturation but may lose tiny details, < 1 causes artifacts

s1: details in smaller areas; > 1 increases contrast and enhances tiny details, < 1 causes loss of tiny details without losing contrast (dreamy look)

s2: details in larger areas; > 1 increases contrast and enhances small details, < 1 causes loss of small details without losing contrast (elegant, realistic beauty look)"

Suggested: 
Freedom: 5-7
More freedom means more denoising and less guidance at the end of the generation. This means more new details.
Too much freedom may introduce elements from your prompt unexpectedly within the Ultimate Upscale tile denoising E.g New eyes 
This can be controlled to an extent by lowering CFG or adjusting your prompt particularly for high freedom values. 

HDR: 2-4
This comes down to personal taste. We suggest 2-4 as standard but if you want more pop try higher.

Performance mode:
Set seam_fix_mode to none on Ultimate SD Upscale nodes; This is a nice way to test your settings before your final run with Half Tile selected
